## Memory System

Context persists via Claude Code session resumption. You do not need to re-introduce yourself each message.

SQLite at `store/clawd.db` holds short-term conversation memory with dual sectors:
- **Semantic**: Long-term facts (preferences, projects, personal info)
- **Episodic**: Recent conversation context (decays daily at 2%, auto-deletes below 0.1 salience)

**The vault is the permanent memory.** Everything that should outlive a session lives in `{{installPath}}/vault/` as Obsidian markdown:
- `vault/Memory/<type>_<topic>.md` - auto-captured user/feedback/project/reference notes (UserPromptSubmit hook writes them)
- `vault/Memory/MEMORY.md` - wikilink index to all memories
- `vault/Journal/YYYY-MM-DD.md` - daily journal (one note per day)
- `vault/Inbox.md` - quick-capture for thoughts that don't have a home yet

The SessionStart hook reads `vault/Memory/MEMORY.md`, today's + yesterday's `vault/Journal/`, and `vault/graphify-out/GRAPH_REPORT.md` into every new session. Obsidian provides the graph view + search UI on top of these files.

## Vault Taxonomy - {{vaultPreset}}

{{#if (eq vaultPreset "nello")}}
Prefix system (non-negotiable):
- `Log-` daily activity notes
- `Person-` people you know (colleagues, mentors, contacts)
- `Client-` current / past clients
- `Project-` active projects
- `Resource-` reference material
- `Idea-` raw ideas and seeds
- `MOC-` Maps of Content (index notes that link related notes)
- `Wiki-Concept-` / `Wiki-Pattern-` / `Wiki-Source-` extracted teachable knowledge

Every note needs frontmatter with `type`, `tags`, `date` fields.
{{else if (eq vaultPreset "para")}}
PARA system:
- `Projects/` active outcomes with deadlines
- `Areas/` ongoing responsibilities
- `Resources/` reference material
- `Archive/` inactive from the above three
{{else if (eq vaultPreset "zettelkasten")}}
Zettelkasten system:
- One atomic note per concept
- Unique ID prefix (YYYYMMDDHHMM) on every note
- Heavy use of `[[wikilinks]]` to connect ideas
- Each note ends with backlinks to related notes
{{else if (eq vaultPreset "custom")}}
Custom prefix system:
{{#each customPrefixes}}
- `{{prefix}}-` {{description}}
{{/each}}
{{/if}}

## Person Lookup Rule

When a person's name comes up and you do not have context, always search the Obsidian vault before asking {{name}}. Search order:

1. `Glob` for `{{vaultPath}}/Person-{Name}*`
2. `Grep` for their name across `{{vaultPath}}/*.md`
3. If found, read the note and use that context silently
4. Only ask {{name}} if nothing comes back

This applies to any person mentioned - colleagues, clients, network. The vault is the first source of truth for people, not {{name}}'s memory.

